node.text:
Fire those LEG & BUTT🔥 - this one is a MUST try if you still at home or no access to weights room. SAVE & TAG your bff 👯‍♀️ - don't be selfish LMAO 😏
.
OKAY, now who else is READY to kick some a** and start the week strong?! 🙋🏻‍♀️ If you are interested in workouts that are EFFECTIVE (no cookie butter plan or magic tricks 🙄 like we can see on the internet) Email me or click link in bio. I only work with the serious ones!
.
Grab your bands and 2 gallon of water, if you have that perfect, if you don't grab something heavy from around!
.
Workout instructions:
.
No rest between exercises
60 sec rest after each rounds
There are 4 total. 
GW = Gallon water E/S= each side
.
1️⃣ GW BANDED PULSES SQUAT WALK - 10 steps total (get 2 low pulses at low squat)
2️⃣ RESISTED BAND 3/4 SUMO SQUATS - 10 total + 10 BANDED JUMPS
push backwards against the bands as you come up - squeeze you butt and abs - you will feel it a LOT
3️⃣ SINGLE LEG HAMMIE LYING CURL - 10 E/S do these slow & controlled, the hamstring and glutei should be fired up 
4️⃣ GW BANDED B-STANCE SQUAT SIDE LEG LIFT - 10 E/S (use a light to medium band - I did use the strongest and then It was too hard LOL.  its about form not else…)
Your bodyweight is on the fix leg, squat down, lift your leg up + squeeze your glutes as you come high. You can tap down the floor to help with balance.
5️⃣ SQUAT BAND SIDE TOE TAPS - 5 reps E/S
(3 taps = 1 rep, so repeat 5x and then move onto the other leg.
6️⃣ LYING SINGLE LEG HAMMIE CURL - 10E/L (husband didn’t do a very good job filming this sorry lol) - do these slow controlled, make sure to feel it in your hamstring!
7️⃣ LYING CURL - 10 leg together - Control those and squeeze at the top🔥
.
Tank top and shirts BACK in stock… 🥳 click the link in my bio 🔗
.
🎶 Nickelback ‘how you Remind me remix’

What workout do you want to see next?

node.text:
Wanted to focus on some important basic moves. It’s not always easy to have to have correct technique as they are involving so much muscles in once and so much concentration. .
.
I could go heavier but as I’m working to perfect my form and my mood was a bit under the weather - my body is hibernating like the Floridian iguanas 🦎 😂 .
.
By working out lighter I could squeeze more my glutes and have the best mind muscles connection everrrr! .
.
How would you rate those exercises on 1-10?? 😅 .
.
TAG a buddy you would do this with 👏👏. I did this with my friend @fitnesswithharvey bonus at the end for the fanatic lol
.

node.text:
Do 3 sets of 15 reps 30 sec rest

Workout description 
1. Start with the abs are they are the foundation of your body, on an decline bench, if you don’t have a ViRP, dumbbell or a bar will do the work too .
.
2. Follow by L-seat ring legs should be 😆 90° or above from the floor. Always keep control of your body. The challenge here is to move and maintain stability: HI SHOULDER MUSCLES! .
.
3. Reverse grip face pull: you fire up not only your back but your core and your Lower body by the isometric contraction...! Super efficient to get your back strong, defined and powerful shoulders!
.
4. Pyramidal deadlift, consists of increasing the weights as set go! Keep your core tight, back remains straight, eyes look in the same direction as your body move up and down (does it make sense? 😅) .
.
5. T bar squat, I do a sumo version  because I felt more comfortable that way. Find the best stance for yourself. Increase weight as well until the last 2-3 reps are difficult.... .
.
⚠️ IF YOU WANT MORE VIDEOS TAG A FRIEND AND COMMENT FIRE 🔥 🔥 🔥

node.text:
.
Since being in France I have doing only cardio and strength work in the water. I have lift zero weight and have been following intuitive diet: every day boil cod 🐟 , egg 🥚 , veggie 🥦 very limited carbs - as I only ate an ice cream, a pain au Chocolat 🥐 , and few little extra stuff 😂 🤫 and I feel AMAZING! Yes you can see I’m not that shredded but I’m honest and I show real! .
.
Know that not it’s all lost! You won’t be fat or lose all your gains. Even if it depends each ones of us. It’s good to have a break, and when I’ll be in Miami all will come back to my routine with super hard training and a super ripped shape! .
.
How do you handle your summer time? Strict diet or relax diet? Tell me below here 👇👇👇 it’s your turn to speak 🙏 .
.
Tag someone to enjoy the 2nd part when I was waiting for the 2nd class - when I’m bored I have fun on my own

node.text:
I got asked what your tattoo represents. Here my explanation: The sun reflects off the dark cloud. To those who can see the top or back of the cloud, the reflection is so bright that the cloud appears to be lined with silver. The sun is always shining. It shines in the day. It shines in the night. It shines when the day is clear. It shines when the clouds are dark. We can’t see the sun at night because it’s on the other side of the earth, but it is still shining. We can’t see the sun when the dark clouds hang low, but the sun is still shining behind the dark clouds, creating a silver lining. In every dark cloud there is a silver lining…. ☀️ 
Plus it brings warmth, fire 🔥 (the one inside of me fighting passionately for something, or burning what’s toxic to me) and with a bit of spirituality it brings me to love ❤️…. 

Do you have tattoos? What do they represent? 

To end on a fun note: 🤪 If you don’t have - tag someone you know with hair (can be a pet - mustache accepted), 4 limbs, who can walk or run, make noise with their mouth, affectionate, who eat a lot or not, who nap but work also… I need to see where all those tags will bring me : SURPRISE 😂 

Happy Wednesday 😙😘

node.text:
You can lift every weight in the gym, but if you can't move your body, what's the point? 

If you’re agreed type 💯 
Tag / share with a friend 🙏

Being able to flex your mobility is an important part of a healthy lifestyle—even if mastering the movements used to hone your abilities isn't always easy.

The challenge that comes with pushing your body to move in new, different ways.. This is a double whammy because it's great warmup exercise and a great bodyweight exercise in general. 

Admittedly, when first doing those crab variations it's a little uncomfortable 😬. We rarely open up our bodies in this position (arms extended back, opening up the chest and hip extension)—which is why it's so deliciously good.

The crab reach can help out anyone with tight hip flexors, particularly those of us who sit all day in an office or don’t stretch enough 😆 since it's a chest and shoulder opener 💯

To perform the move, you just need some space on the floor to spread out. Start out with the crab lift and upgrade to the crab reach 👍 3 sets of 10 reps (gradually you’ll change as you’ll get stronger!

For CUSTOMIZED Male / Female Training program or diet email me to LINDADURBESSON.COM 

—— 👉 More videos tips at @LDFITworkout @LDFITstore

I’ve spent half of my life not allowing myself to be happy unless and until… But the unless and until never came perfect each time.  So I was waiting. Eventually I realized that you will never be happy until you have the ability to be happy with what you have. Right now. In the moment.

Striving for more in a thing but waiting for the perfect moment - that will never come its another. As you build a better life, this ability is a practice. A daily one. Because we all snap back to tying our happy to things we dont have and event that havent happened. 

Accept your story. Where you are at in life and everything that lead you to here. Nothing is permanent. Appreciate and give yourself credit on how far you have come. Anything is possible even if it hasn’t happen yet. Trust your process and do the best you can. It always workout if it means to be right? 

If you relate double tap and comment Y-E-S letter by letter without being interrupted or tag a friend (still to work on maintaining this high algorithm of mine) 😜 

Online coaching LindaDurbesson.com @ldfitstore @ldfitworkout

Life will throw unexpected curveballs at you. Don't let these throw you off course. Any challenge can be an opportunity to grow. It's all about perspective. Don't let discouragement keep you from receiving all the wisdom and growth the challenge brings. If you don't quit, you win. #lindadurbesson

If you did or would like to do like in the pic comment 💯💯💯 🤭😜

node.text:
HEY YOUUUU - stop scrolling like a mad man for a second 😜
A leap of faith 🙏 Train your brain to start acknowledging the good in your life.  Not just events but also people.  Remember, your life isn’t just a direct manifestation of your thoughts but also how you think. 💭💛
Tell me what you were doing & how is your Sunday ? 
Wearing @fitjeans 

🇫🇷 He toi arrête une seconde j’ai qqch à te dire 😜
Un acte de foi .. Entraînez votre cerveau et commencer à reconnaître le positif dans votre vie. Pas seulement des événements mais aussi avec les personnes autour de vous. N'oubliez pas que votre vie n'est pas seulement une manifestation directe de vos pensées, mais aussi de votre façon de penser. 💙🤍❤️ Dites moi ce que vous faisiez juste avant et quoi de beau en ce dimanche? 

🇵🇹 Oye gente... sí, deténgase un segundo 🙏 
Um salto de fé. Treine seu cérebro e comece a reconhecer o que há de positivo em sua vida. Não apenas eventos, mas também com as pessoas ao seu redor. Lembre-se de que sua vida não é apenas uma manifestação direta de seus pensamentos, mas também da maneira como você pensa 💚💛💚 Diga-me o que você estava fazendo um pouco antes e que fazem neste domingo?

🇪🇸 Amigas, amigos, para lo que haces… Un acto de fe siiii!! Piensas a entrenar tbm tu cerebro y a reconocer lo positivo en tu vida. No solo eventos, sino también a las personas que te rodean. Recuerda que tu vida no es solo una manifestación directa de tus pensamientos, sino también de tu forma de pensar. ❤️💛❤️ Dime qué estabas haciendo justo antes y qué tal en este domingo? 

🇮🇹 Amici della Italia, per quello che fate adesso? 
L'atto di fede.... Pensi ad allenare il tuo cervello e riconoscere il positivo nella tua vita. Non solo eventi, ma anche le persone intorno a te. Ricordate che la tua vita non è solo una manifestazione diretta dei tuoi pensieri, ma anche di tuo modo di pensare. 💚🤍❤️ Dimmi cosa facevi poco adesso e che faceva EN questa domenica?

I could call this the “HOT BODY SUMMER” why? Well you don’t need equipments and you can do it anywhere at the beach 🏖 or in your backyard 💪

The matter is to do 30 reps x 4 sets then rest 60 sec in between slides. 

As you can see at my face and my excecution tents to get slower as I go! if you do it right you’ll end like me. ☠️ 😂 

Tag with someone you could do this with - like - share & comment! Help with the engagement as this won’t show as much as someone else naked pic hahahaah!

Do you want more of this??? Type YES 👍 or what you’d like to see Instead. 

How was your 4th of July 🇺🇸?

node.text:
You may see a woman smiling, but I see a woman with hard work. I see a powerful person who never surrender, fight every battles in front of her. A woman able to share confidence, even in her worsted moments. Not because of the body I’ve build, but by the person I’ve become along the way. 💪

If those words reaches out to you like home. Feel free to share it & mentioned your friends. 

Ok. Now. Wanna hear a joke about construction 🚧?? 
I’m still working on it🤣🤣 

Oh you still reading… 🤓😬 After breaking the ice with that badwy joke…… I’m here to help if you have questions regarding training, diet, mental health, or want simply advices. Now if you want something a personalized guidance I have new spots available for my online personal training - ⚡️Click the link in my bio ⚡️

node.text:
So many years I’ve spent at war with this body. For what? 😩

When all it does is work every single day to keep me alive and well? It can be a daily practice to unlearn what society has told us is beautiful and desirable.

It’s been a journey to hold my heart, mind, energy, and soul to the same standard of importance as I always did my body.

There were years where this softness around my hips and thighs would’ve caused me to feel less than, stripping me of my self worth and confidence.

Today, I say, “look at that woman, her shell woven with equal parts soft and strong.” ☀️ The body may provide your energy and intellect but it will never be your body that keeps people around— those worth having around anyways. 

DO YOU KNOW SOMEONE WHO THINK THAT WAY TOO? TYPE YES & TAG THEM 😎

And now it’s time for some outdoor cardio between rains storms 😂 to test this hybrid E-bike from @lifeevehicles - getting excited because something big is coming where I’ll continue to another level to help people a different way. ❤️
